Files in this directory, in rough order of suggested reading:

General:

    README - this file
    Intro.txt - introduction to MUDs in general, and this MUD in particular
    Playing.txt - how to play in this MUD in particular
    Building.txt - how to build stuff in this MUD scenario
    Decisions.txt - some decisions I've made
    ToDo.txt - things I might eventually do
    simple.m - a full, but very simple scenario (source form)
    esperanto.m - the same, but using Esperanto instead of English

Specific to the Amiga software:

    MUD.txt - the custom client
    MUDCre.txt - the small program which creates an empty database
    MUDServ.txt - the server, including info for administrators
    SMUD.txt - the small text-only direct client
    Agents.txt - the various agents (serial port, TCP/IP)
    Images.txt - info on the many images I would like

Documentation for those wanting to program within the system:

    Programming.txt - description of the AmigaMUD programming language
    ProgConcepts.txt - general introduction to the concepts used
    Builtins.txt - the builtin functions in the system
    Scenario.txt - explanation and guide to the full scenario sources

Other (release notes for the various releases):

    ChangesFromV0.5
    ChangesFromV0.6
    ChangesFromV0.7
    ChangesFromV0.9
    ChangesFromV1.0
